# Server Actions Rules

## Structure
- Place actions in `features/<feature>/actions.ts`
- Always add `"use server"` at the top
- Validate all inputs with Zod before processing
- Check session + RBAC at the start of every action
- Return typed results: `{ success: true, data } | { success: false, error: string }`

## Template

```tsx
"use server"

import { z } from "zod"
import { getSession } from "@/lib/auth"
import { db } from "@/lib/prisma"

const schema = z.object({ ... })

export async function myAction(input: unknown) {
    const session = await getSession()
    if (!session) return { success: false, error: "Unauthorized" }
    const parsed = schema.safeParse(input)
    if (!parsed.success) return { success: false, error: parsed.error.message }
    try {
        const result = await db....
        return { success: true, data: result }
    } catch (err) {
        console.error(err)
        return { success: false, error: "Something went wrong" }
    }
}
```

## API Routes
- Use only for: webhooks, external callbacks, file streaming, SSE
- For everything else, prefer Server Actions
- Always validate request body with Zod
- Always check auth before processing
- Never expose internal error messages to the client

